Constructor:
1. In python, __init__ is known as constructor
2. It is used to initialize the state/properties of an object
3. We don't have to call the init method explicitly, During object creating, it will automatically get invoked
4. In case of __init__, please make sure that the first argument should be "self".
5. "self" will refer the current execution context (Currently created object's address).
6. If we want, we can use any other variable name in place of "self". But according to the industrial standard rules, we should use "self"




